description: Smooth Vanilla 500ml; Smooth and creamy vanilla just got a whole lot more exciting at 290 calories per tub. Introducing new Breyers Delights, a revolutionary lower calorie ice cream for healthy lifestyle enthusiasts which not only tastes great, but has only 290-350 calories per tub (yep, that's per tub) , lower sugar, up to 20g of protein and is made with fresh cream. What do we do to make our healthy ice cream taste so good; Each tub of high protein ice cream contains 20g of milk protein from two naturally occurring milk proteins; casein and whey. A naturally sourced sweetener, derived from the leaves of the Stevia rebaudiana plant, we use a highly purified extract of the Stevia leaf to give our icecream the sweetness it needs, which means less sugar and less calories per serving. Fresh cream gives our ice cream its deliciously creamy taste and texture. We believe in making the impossible possible by creating a reduced sugar ice cream tub that allows you to limit your calorie intake whilst treating yourself - without compromising on taste. For more information on our lower calorie, deliciously healthy treat range, please visit our website www. breyersdelights. co. uk or follow us on Instagram @BreyersDelightsUK. Storage temperature: -18°C
name: Breyers Smooth Vanilla Ice Cream 500ML

description: Biryani Masala spice mix with garlic and ginger. Biryani Recipe (Rice with Meat) . Meat (Mutton, Chicken or Beef) 750 gms - 1 kg Basmati Rice (soaked for 30 minutes) 500 - 750 gms (For more/hot masala use 500 gms rice). Onion (medium sized, finely sliced) 4 (250 gms). Tomatoes (medium sized, chopped) 4 (250 gms). Yogurt (beaten) 1 1/2 cup (250 gms). Cooking Oil/Ghee 1 1/2 cup (250 gms). Laziza Biryani Masala one bag only. Optional: chopped Green Coriander 1/2 bunch (1/2 cup), Mint Leaves 1/2 bunch (1/2 cup) & Green Chillies medium whole 6-10. EASY STEPS. 1. Fry onion till it becomes golden brown. Put meat, Laziza Biryani Masala (one bag), tomatoes and fry/cook for 5-10 minutes. Now add yogurt and fry for a while. Add 1-2 glasses of water, cover and cook on low flame till the meat is tender & ghee/oil separates. (In case of chicken do not add water if need arises put only 1 cup water). If masala is not thick then cook further on high flame. 2. Separately boil rice in 12 glasses of hot water & with 3-4 tablespoons of salt till half done. 3. Now form one layer of rice and onto it the second layer of meat masala & green masala (optional) then form onto it third layer of rice. 4. Put it on low flame and let simmer for 15-30 minutes or till rice is tender. Mix well before serving. Serve with Laziza Plum Chutney, raita and salad.
name: Laziza Biryani Plain Mix 100G
